column5: I hear the Temagami shoal map is useful tool to have while on my 6 nights fishing/camping trip in August. Unfortunately it seems to be priced very high at $25. All the other maps for the area were in the $6-$7 and I got the camping map from the Temagami Chamber of Commerce. Wandering if anyone has the shoal map scanned or maybe an old copy I can borrow for a week?  Thanks in advance.   Cheers, Ice Fisherman
It is expensive because it is a huge lake, well worth it to have though because of the many shoals. I,ll see if I still have mine and will let you know. YB
Thanks Bud. I know it's a good map....or so every one says, just that I am not sure how often I'll be able to make it all the way to Temagami and use the map.  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
get one for sure,,,may save your motor,,,and if your not sure of the lake,,,go slow,,,they'll come up from a hundred feet to zero in no time ,,,right out in the middle sometimes
I have 3 Temagami maps (fishing map, navigation and campsite map and the island of Temagami map) your welcome to borrow them for a week if you'd like. YB
Your on Holiday Emile,spend some money
I have been fishing Temagami once or twice a year for 20 years now, if you buy the map I will buy it back off you, I could really use it.  Maybe try some new spots intead of the old favorites!
